Reasoning: The paper introduces an epistemic logic of categories and agents' perception, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses formalizations of concepts from psychological, sociological, and organizational research, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a Kripke-style semantics, which is relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
